---
import SiteLayout from "../../../layouts/SiteLayout.astro";
---

<SiteLayout
  title="Technology | PoliceConduct.org"
  pagePath="/partner/technology/"
>
  <main class="flex-grow-1">
    <section class="py-vh-3 bg-gray-100 border-bottom border-dark">
      <div class="container">
        <nav aria-label="Breadcrumb">
          <ol class="breadcrumb mb-3">
            <li class="breadcrumb-item">
              <a class="link-dark" href="/partner/">Partners</a>
            </li>
            <li class="breadcrumb-item active" aria-current="page">
              Technology
            </li>
          </ol>
        </nav>
        <div class="row g-4 align-items-end">
          <div class="col-12 col-lg-8">
            <p class="text-uppercase small text-muted mb-2">
              Value proposition
            </p>
            <h1 class="display-4 fw-bold">
              Scaling the Infrastructure of Truth
            </h1>
            <p class="lead text-muted mb-0">
              Powering data sovereignty and algorithmic accountability for civic
              tech partners.
            </p>
          </div>
          <div class="col-12 col-lg-4">
            <div class="card shadow-sm rounded-0 border-dark">
              <div class="card-body d-flex flex-column gap-2">
                <div class="text-uppercase small text-muted">Built for</div>
                <div class="fw-semibold">
                  Technology companies and civic tech teams
                </div>
                <div class="text-muted small">
                  Solve the metadata and scale problem for public accountability
                  records.
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="py-vh-2">
      <div class="container">
        <div class="row g-4">
          <div class="col-12 col-lg-7">
            <h2 class="h4 fw-semibold">
              1. Evidence integrity and metadata preservation
            </h2>
            <p class="text-muted">
              The true value of digital evidence is in the metadata. We partner
              with storage and forensic tech teams to preserve timestamps,
              device IDs, and GPS data for court-ready evidence.
            </p>
            <ul class="list-unstyled mb-0 d-flex flex-column gap-2">
              <li>Digital chain-of-custody protocols with secure hashing.</li>
              <li>
                Metadata persistence to survive Fourth Amendment challenges.
              </li>
              <li>Standard sidecar files for court-admissible evidence.</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
          <div class="col-12 col-lg-5">
            <div class="card shadow-sm rounded-0 border-dark h-100">
              <div class="card-body d-flex flex-column gap-3">
                <div class="text-uppercase small text-muted">
                  Partnership pitch
                </div>
                <p class="mb-0">
                  Help us build the standard sidecar for public evidence so
                  user-submitted video remains verifiably untouched.
                </p>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="py-vh-2 bg-light border-top border-bottom border-dark">
      <div class="container">
        <h2 class="h4 fw-semibold mb-3">
          2. Open data standards: the accountability API
        </h2>
        <p class="text-muted">
          Public records remain fragmented across thousands of agencies. We are
          defining a unified schema for misconduct investigation reports and
          Brady/Giglio data.
        </p>
        <div class="row g-4">
          <div class="col-12 col-lg-6">
            <div class="card shadow-sm rounded-0 border-dark h-100">
              <div class="card-body d-flex flex-column gap-2">
                <p class="text-uppercase small text-muted mb-1">
                  Schema standardization
                </p>
                <h3 class="h6 fw-semibold">End data silos</h3>
                <p class="mb-0">
                  Build a universal API that enables cross-jurisdictional search
                  and automation.
                </p>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="col-12 col-lg-6">
            <div class="card shadow-sm rounded-0 border-dark h-100">
              <div class="card-body d-flex flex-column gap-2">
                <p class="text-uppercase small text-muted mb-1">
                  Interoperability
                </p>
                <h3 class="h6 fw-semibold">Design for scale</h3>
                <p class="mb-0">
                  Give researchers and legal teams consistent, queryable data at
                  national scale.
                </p>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="py-vh-2">
      <div class="container">
        <h2 class="h4 fw-semibold mb-3">
          3. Responsible automation and civic AI
        </h2>
        <p class="text-muted">
          As we scale, manual review becomes impossible. We need explainable
          automation that centers on trust, privacy, and human oversight.
        </p>
        <div class="row g-4">
          <div class="col-12 col-lg-4">
            <div class="card shadow-sm rounded-0 border-dark h-100">
              <div class="card-body d-flex flex-column gap-2">
                <h3 class="h6 fw-semibold">Automated redaction</h3>
                <p class="mb-0">
                  Rapidly scrub home addresses and sensitive personal data while
                  preserving evidentiary integrity.
                </p>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="col-12 col-lg-4">
            <div class="card shadow-sm rounded-0 border-dark h-100">
              <div class="card-body d-flex flex-column gap-2">
                <h3 class="h6 fw-semibold">Trend detection</h3>
                <p class="mb-0">
                  Identify heat map spikes in specific misconduct types without
                  black-box models.
                </p>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="col-12 col-lg-4">
            <div class="card shadow-sm rounded-0 border-dark h-100">
              <div class="card-body d-flex flex-column gap-2">
                <h3 class="h6 fw-semibold">Explainable models</h3>
                <p class="mb-0">
                  Build trust-first automation with human oversight and ethical
                  governance.
                </p>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="py-vh-2 bg-gray-100 border-top border-dark">
      <div class="container">
        <h2 class="h4 fw-semibold mb-3">4. Tech stack and collaboration</h2>
        <div class="table-responsive">
          <table class="table table-bordered align-middle">
            <thead class="table-light">
              <tr>
                <th scope="col">Feature</th>
                <th scope="col">Tech partner opportunity</th>
                <th scope="col">Scalability impact</th>
              </tr>
            </thead>
            <tbody>
              <tr>
                <td><strong>Encrypted evidence vaults</strong></td>
                <td>Secure storage and 2026-compliant MFA integration.</td>
                <td>Protect chain of custody for litigation.</td>
              </tr>
              <tr>
                <td><strong>Schema standardization</strong></td>
                <td>Universal JSON/XML formats for MIR records.</td>
                <td>Enable national-scale research and lead generation.</td>
              </tr>
              <tr>
                <td><strong>Privacy-preserving AI</strong></td>
                <td>On-device or edge redaction tools.</td>
                <td>Respect 2026 privacy mandates at scale.</td>
              </tr>
              <tr>
                <td><strong>Audit logs</strong></td>
                <td>Immutable change logs for access and edits.</td>
                <td>Guarantee integrity for legal and bar partners.</td>
              </tr>
            </tbody>
          </table>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="py-vh-2">
      <div class="container">
        <div
          class="d-flex flex-column flex-lg-row align-items-lg-center justify-content-between gap-3"
        >
          <div>
            <h2 class="h4 fw-semibold mb-1">
              Ready to define the open data schema?
            </h2>
            <p class="text-muted mb-0">
              We can share a technical specifications abstract for civic tech
              leads and CTOs.
            </p>
          </div>
          <a
            class="btn btn-dark rounded-0"
            href="/about/contact?whoami=Partner&message=I%27m%20interested%20in%20the%20PoliceConduct%20Open%20Data%20Schema%20and%20a%20technical%20specifications%20abstract."
          >
            Request the technical brief
          </a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>
  </main>
</SiteLayout>
